data.title: Wikipedia:WikiProject France
data.text:
Welcome to WikiProject France. We are a group of editors dedicated to improving Wikipedia's coverage of France and Monaco related articles, through collaboration and cooperation. If you would like to join us, please add your username to the members list.

Scope

WikiProject France concerns coordination, creation, development, and organization of efforts on all articles related to France and Monaco.

Goals

Get this project organized.

To serve as a central point of discussion for collaboration related to France/Monaco. Foster increased cooperation between editors in order to meet the other goals.

To create the foremost reliable and accurate free-content encyclopedia of France/Monaco in the English language.

Build all Top Importance France Articles to Good Article status, at a minimum (FA is preferred). Current progress: 10 out of 108 articles meet this criteria.

If you can help with any of these topics, please add your name to the third column

WikiProject France Quick Help Table

Do you need help with the proper format of France/French terms or translations? See the Manual of Style links below:

The France & French-related Manual of Style covers:

General Rules

Orthography, covers accents, ligatures, and sorting.

Naming Conventions, including noble titles, works of art, and place names.

Administrative Conventions, covers political and geographic divisions within France.

Transportation Conventions, Rail/Tram naming and terms (including SNCF related guidelines)

Members can add one of the following userboxes to their userpage.

There are at this time two barnstars, one for France and the other for French Guiana, which might be given out to editors who make substantial contributions to articles in their specific field. A template is available for awarding a barnstar to users, more information about it is available at WikiProject France/Barnstar.
